value.value: 外転神経形態異常
any structural anomaly of the sixth cranial nerve, which originates in the abducens nucleus of the pons and sends motor fibers to the lateral rectus muscles of the eye
顔面神経の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the sensory and motor nerve that supplies the muscles of facial expression and the expression and taste at the anterior two-thirds of the tongue; principal branches are the superficial opthalmic, buccal, palatine and hyomandibular
内耳神経の形態異常

any structural anomaly in the composite sensory nerve innervating the receptor cells of the membranous labyrinth; it consists of two major, anatomically and functionally distinct components, each of which have different central connections: the vestibular nerve and the cochlear nerve
舌咽神経の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the sensory and autonomic axons to the parotid gland, carotid body, posterior third of the tongue; the branchial motor component contains motor fibers that innervate muscles that elevate the pharynx and larynx, and the tympanic branch supplies parasympathetic fibers to the otic ganglion
迷走神経の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the autonomic, sensory and motor axons of the tenth cranial nerve; it is primarily sensory but also has visceromotor components; it originates in the brain stem and controls many autonomic functions of the heart, lungs, stomach, pharynx, larynx, trachea, esophagus and other gastrointestinal tract components, and also controls some motor functions such as speech; the sensory branches mediate sensation from the pharynx, larynx, thorax and abdomen; it also innervates taste buds in the epiglottis
副神経形態異常
any structural anomaly of the eleventh cranial nerve, which normally originates from neurons in the medulla and in the cervical spinal cord
舌下神経の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the motor nerve which innervates all the intrinsic and all but one of the extrinsic muscles of the tongue
脊髄神経の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the any of the 31 paired peripheral nerves formed by the union of the dorsal and ventral spinal roots from each spinal cord segment
横隔神経の形態異常
any structural anomaly of motor, sensory and sympathetic neuron axons that project to the diaphragm and other tissues
横隔神経の欠如
absence of the motor, sensory and sympathetic neuron axons that project to the diaphragm and other tissues
横隔神経の非束状化
misprojection or failure to bundle the motor, sensory and sympathetic neuron axons that project to the diaphragm and other tissues
頭蓋神経節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the groups of nerve cell bodies associated with the twelve cranial nerves
膝神経節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the facial nerve (seventh cranial nerve)
膝神経節の矮小化
reduced size of the geniculate ganglion or decreased size of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the facial nerve
錐体神経節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the larger, lower group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the glossopharyngeal nerve
錐体神経節の矮小化
reduced size of the lower group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the glossopharyngeal nerve
錐体神経節の欠如
absence of the lower group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the glossopharyngeal nerve
下神経節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the large group of sensory neuron cell bodies, anterior to the jugular vein, associated with the vagus nerve (tenth cranial nerve)
下神経節の矮小化
reduced size of the large group of sensory neuron cell bodies, anterior to the jugular vein, associated with the vagus nerve (tenth cranial nerve)
下神経節の欠如
absence of the large group of sensory neuron cell bodies, anterior to the jugular vein, associated with the vagus nerve (tenth cranial nerve)
三叉神経節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the trigeminal nerve (fifth cranial nerve)
三叉神経節の矮小化
reduced size of the trigeminal ganglion
三叉神経節肥大
increased bulk size due to increased cell size of the trigeminal ganglion
三叉神経節の巨大化
increased size of the group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the trigeminal nerve
舌咽神経節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the two groups of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the ninth cranial nerve
上舌咽神経節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the upper, smaller ganglion of the glossopharyngeal nerve located at the jugular foramen
上舌咽神経節の矮小化
reduced size of the upper ganglion of the glossopharyngeal nerve located at the jugular foramen
上舌咽神経節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the vagus nerve
上迷走神経節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the upper ganglion of the vagus nerve located at the jugular foramen
上迷走神経節の矮小化
reduced size of the upper ganglion of the vagus nerve located at the jugular foramen
末梢神経系グリア細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of non-neuronal cells that form the myelin insulation of nervous pathways, guide neuronal migration during development, and exchange metabolites with neurons
シュワン細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the cells which form the insulating myelin sheaths of peripheral axons
シュワン細胞数の減少
fewer than normal number of cells that sheath the axons of the peripheral nervous system
シュワン細胞の欠如
missing cells that sheath the axons of the peripheral nervous system
シュワン細胞前駆体の欠如
missing progenitors of cells that sheath the axons of the peripheral nervous system
生殖腺の矮小化
reduced size of the testis or the ovary
配偶子の欠如
absence of mature reproductive cells, ovum or spermatozoon, capable of fusing with a cell of similar origin, but opposite sex to give a zygote
雌性生殖組織の異常
any structural anomaly of the organs associated with producing offspring in the gender that bears the offspring
子宮の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the female muscular organ of gestation in which the developing embryo or fetus is nourished until birth
子宮の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the uterus, typically resulting in decreased size
子宮拡張
stretched or widened luminal space of the female muscular organ of gestation
配偶子異常
anomaly of any mature reproductive cell, ovum or spermatozoon, capable of fusing with a cell of similar origin, but opposite sex, to produce a zygote
卵母細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the mature germ cells in the female
卵巣の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the female reproductive gland containing the germ cells
卵巣の矮小化
reduced size of the female reproductive gland containing the germ cells
卵巣の過形成
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the ovary, typically resulting in increased size
卵胞形成障害
a block in the formation of the spherical ovum in the ovary
卵胞形成異常
atypical formation or failure to form the spherical ovum in the ovary
卵胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the sac-like structure in the ovary which surrounds an ovum
成熟した卵胞の欠如

absence of ovarian follicles that are ready for ovulation and present a blanched spot (the follicular stigma) where the graafian follicle is about to rupture on the surface of the ovary; a first maturation (meiotic) division of the primary oocyte usually occurs just prior to rupture of the follicle
